 agarwal born   january  age  patna bihar india residence london england citizenship indian occupation chairman of vedanta resources known for the vedanta foundation net worth  billion  spouses kiran agarwal children   agnivesh son and priya daughter website wwwvedantaresourcescom anil agarwal is the founder and chairman of vedanta resources plc he controls vedanta resources plc through volcan investments a holding vehicle with a  stake in the business contents  early life  career  controversy and criticism  philanthropy  honours and awards  references  external links early lifeedit he was born and brought up in patna india he studied at miller high school but quit school at  to join his fathers business making aluminium conductors at  he left pune for mumbai then bombay to explore career opportunities careeredit in the mids he began trading in scrap metal collecting it from cable companies in other states and selling it in mumbai in  anil agarwal acquired shamsher sterling corporation a manufacturer of enameled copper among other products with a bank loan for the next  years he ran both businesses in  he set up a factory to manufacture jellyfilled cables creating sterlite industries he soon realized that the profitability of his business was volatile fluctuating with the prices of his raw materials copper and aluminium so he decided to control his input costs by manufacturing the metals instead of buying them in  sterlite industries became the first private sector company in india to set up a copper smelter and refinery in  sterlite industries acquired madras aluminium a ‘sick’ company that had been shut down for  years and held by the board for industrial and financial reconstruction bifr the next step of the backward integration process seemed natural mining his first opportunity came when the government announced a disinvestment program in  he acquired  percent in bharat aluminium company balco a public sector undertaking in the very next year he acquired a majority stake nearly  per cent in staterun hzl both the companies were considered sleepy and inefficient mining firms to access international capital markets anil agarwal and his team incorporated vedanta resources plc in  at the time of its listing vedanta resources plc was the first indian firm to be listed on london stock exchange on december   vedanta resources became the parent company of the group through a process of internal restructuring of group companies and their shareholding in  vedanta resources plc announced a global bond offering and acquired konkola copper mines in zambia africa in  vedanta resources acquired a controlling stake in sesa goa limited india’s largest producerexporter of iron ore and in  the company acquired south african miner anglo american’s portfolio of zinc assets in namibia ireland and south africa the next year vedanta resources acquired controlling stake in cairn india india’s largest private sector oilproducing firm the merger of sesa goa and sterlite industries was announced in  as part of the vedanta group’s consolidation vedanta resources headquartered in london is a globally diversified natural resources conglomerate with interests in zinc lead silver copper iron ore aluminium power generation and oil and gas the greatest share of its assets however is in england agarwal lives in india but his heart and soul are in london his philanthropic activities are targeted at eradicating poverty by creating jobs and contributing to uks gdp growth through his business operations controversy and criticismedit in  a committee of the indian supreme court charged that vedanta had dumped thousands of tons of arsenicbearing slag near its factory in the indian state of tamil nadu resulting in major poisoning of the environment and neighbouring population in  another committee of the indian supreme court charged that vedanta had forced over one hundred indigenous families from their homes in the indian state of odisha where it sought to mine bauxite according to the committees report “an atmosphere of fear was created through the hired goons” and residents were “beaten up by the employees of ms vedanta” vedanta’s actions in odisha were rebuked by the british commerce agency and the church of england investment funds sold their shares in the company in protest in zambia vedanta dumped hazardous waste into the kafue river from its copper mine there according to a lawsuit filed by  residents resulting in widespread human illness and the death of fish a local judge stated this was lack of corporate responsibility and criminal and a tipping point for corporate recklessness” in  an audit was begun by zambian officials due to suspicions that vedanta has not been paying its proper fees to the government in addition hundreds of former mine workers are fighting vedanta for severance or disability pay philanthropyedit in  anil agarwal created the vedanta foundation as the vehicle through which the group companies would carry out their philanthropic programs and activities in the financial year  the vedanta group companies and the vedanta foundation invested us million in building hospitals schools and infrastructure conserving the environment and funding community programs that improve health education and livelihood of over  million people the initiatives were undertaken in partnership with the government and nongovernmental organizations ngos among his inspirations agarwal counts andrew carnegie and david rockefeller who built public works with their fortunes and bill gates the activities funded by his philanthropy are focused on child welfare women empowerment and education anil agarwal was ranked second in hurun india philanthropy list  for his personal donation of rs crore about  million he was ranked th in the hurun india rich list with a personal fortune of cr agarwal has pledged to donate  of his family’s wealth to charity saying he was inspired by bill gates honours and awardsedit the economic times business leader award –  mining journal lifetime achievement award   the ernst  young entrepreneur of the year   the asian awards entrepreneur of the year   vedanta was stripped of international safety awards after it was found it failed to declare its involvement one of the worst industrial accidents in indias history referencesedit   anil agarwal forbes retrieved  june    leadership vedanta   srikar muthyala  september  the list of great entrepreneurs of india in  mybtechlife archived from the original on  january    a b httpswwwtheguardiancombusinesssepvedantahumanrightsissuesindia  a b anil agarwal pledges  of his wealth to charity business standard  september    lunch with bs  anil agarwal business standard  december    vedanta founder is a daring deccan herald  august    profile  anil agarwal the guardian  july    dont be too smart looking foolish is ok rediff money  february    anil agarwal on simplicity and determination at vedanta resources bcgperspectives  march    anil agarwals big bang theory forbes  august    bold baron india today  september    madras aluminium company limited my iris   vedanta may offer  higher price for hzl balco stake economic times  august    vedanta resources formally lists on lse rediff  december    vedanta resources plc announces pricing for  bn bond business standard  may    vedanta buys zambia mine business standard  august    vedanta buys sesa goa for  m business standard  april    vedanta to buy uk firms zinc assets for  bn business standard  may    vedanta completes deal with cairn india business standard  december    sesa goa sterlite merger becomes effective times of india  august    vedanta resources forbes may    httpswwwnytimescomnyregionstreamofforeignwealthflowstotimewarnercondoshtml  sesa sterlite wins asian csr leadership award the navhind times  october    hurun india philanthropy list  hurun  november    vedanta mining tycoon anil agarwal vows to give away fortune the times  september    et awards  anil agarwal is the bu